---
import LegalLayout from "../components/LegalLayout.astro";

const sections = [
  ["about-the-site", "About the Site"], ["forward-looking-statements", "Forward-looking statements"],
  ["eligibility", "Eligibility"], ["permitted-use", "Permitted use"], ["intellectual-property", "Intellectual property"],
  ["user-submissions", "User submissions"], ["third-party-links", "Third-party links"], ["warranties", "Warranties"],
  ["liability", "Liability"], ["indemnification", "Indemnification"], ["governing-law", "Governing law"], ["changes", "Changes"], ["contact", "Contact"],
].map(([id, label]) => ({ id, label }));
---

<LegalLayout title="Terms of Service" effectiveDate="April 21, 2026" description="The terms governing access to and use of rangeway.co and related subdomains." sections={sections}>
  <p>Rangeway Energy, Inc. ("Rangeway," "we," "us," or "our") operates the website at rangeway.co and related subdomains (collectively, the "Site"). These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your access to and use of the Site. By accessing or using the Site, you agree to be bound by these Terms.</p>

  <h2 id="about-the-site">1. About the Site</h2>
  <p>The Site provides information about Rangeway, including our network of EV charging and hospitality locations, partners, team, and business. The Site is informational in nature. It does not facilitate bookings, purchases, account creation, or financial transactions.</p>

  <h2 id="forward-looking-statements">2. Forward-Looking Statements</h2>
  <p>The Site contains forward-looking statements about Rangeway's business, including planned site locations, network formats, partnerships, and target opening dates. These statements reflect our current plans and beliefs but are not binding commitments. Actual outcomes may differ due to site permitting, construction timelines, partner negotiations, financing conditions, regulatory approvals, and other factors. Nothing on the Site should be relied upon as a promise of future operations, specific site openings, or financial performance.</p>

  <h2 id="eligibility">3. Eligibility</h2>
  <p>The Site is not directed to children under 13, and we do not knowingly collect information from children under 13. By using the Site, you represent that you are at least 13 years old.</p>

  <h2 id="permitted-use">4. Permitted Use</h2>
  <p>You may access and use the Site for personal, non-commercial purposes. You may not:</p>
  <ul><li>Copy, reproduce, distribute, or create derivative works from Site content without our written permission, except as permitted by applicable fair use or fair dealing principles</li><li>Use any automated means (bots, scrapers, crawlers) to access the Site in ways that interfere with its normal operation</li><li>Attempt to gain unauthorized access to any part of the Site, its servers, or related systems</li><li>Use the Site to transmit malware, spam, or other harmful content</li><li>Use the Site in any way that violates applicable law</li></ul>

  <h2 id="intellectual-property">5. Intellectual Property</h2>
  <p>All content on the Site, including text, images, graphics, logos, and the Rangeway name and marks, is the property of Rangeway Energy, Inc. or its licensors and is protected by U.S. and international intellectual property laws. Partner logos and marks displayed on the Site are the property of their respective owners and are used with permission.</p>

  <h2 id="user-submissions">6. User Submissions</h2>
  <p>If you contact us through the Site (for example, by submitting the contact form or subscribing to Field Notes), you grant us permission to use the information you provide to respond to you, route your inquiry internally, and maintain ordinary business records. We do not publish, share, or sell your submissions. Our use of personal information is further described in our <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.</p>

  <h2 id="third-party-links">7. Third-Party Links and Services</h2>
  <p>The Site links to third-party websites and uses third-party services (including our partners, newsletter platform, and analytics provider). We are not responsible for the content, policies, or practices of third-party sites or services. Your use of any third-party site or service is at your own risk and subject to the terms and policies of that third party.</p>

  <h2 id="warranties">8. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
